# Repo-root .dockerignore — applied to ALL builds whose context is the
# repo root (currently: workers/render image and apps/api image, both via
# infra/docker-compose.yml). Without this, the ~1.5G working tree
# (including .git, infra/.env, _bmad-output/, node_modules, build caches)
# would be sent to the docker daemon as build context, slowing builds
# and risking secret leaks in image layers.
#
# Strategy: deny-by-default at the directory level, then allowlist the
# narrow paths each Dockerfile actually COPYs from. Paths NOT listed
# here continue to be sent to the build context (Docker uses
# allowlist-via-negation: leading `!` re-includes after a broader
# exclude pattern).

# --- Always exclude --------------------------------------------------------
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.dockerignore
.github

# Editor / OS noise
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo

# BMAD planning + scheduling artifacts (gitignored too, but we must
# also keep them out of the Docker build context to avoid surprise
# leaks of operator-internal docs into image layers if anyone ever
# accidentally copies "everything").
_bmad-output
.claude
.codex
.worktrees

# Test + coverage output
.pytest_cache
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/.venv
coverage
.coverage
test-results
playwright-report
.playwright-mcp

# Frontend build / dependency caches
node_modules
.pnpm-store
**/dist
**/build
**/*.tsbuildinfo
apps/web/vite.config.js
apps/web/vite.config.d.ts

# Local env / secret files (never include in any image layer)
.env
.env.local
.env.production
infra/.env
infra/.last-verify
infra/.last-verify-runbook

# Docs not needed at runtime EXCEPT the agent runbook (re-included below
# for the apps/api Dockerfile's COPY step).
docs/**
!docs/agents-add-model-runbook.md
